      ],
      "summary": "The American Imams Academy is a specialized educational institution dedicated to developing the next generation of Muslim community leaders in the United States. The organization provides <cite id=\"1\">higher education in Islamic theology and Da\u2019wah</cite> to equip imams and community leaders with the academic and spiritual tools necessary for modern ministry. In the 2023 fiscal year, the academy reported <cite id=\"2\">total revenue of $824,033</cite>, which was primarily sourced from <cite id=\"3\">individual contributions</cite>. While the organization maintains a focused mission, it experienced a <cite id=\"4\">revenue decline of approximately 11%</cite> compared to the previous year. Despite this fluctuation, the academy operates with a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 70.2%</cite>, ensuring that the majority of its budget supports its core academic offerings. These programs include a <cite id=\"6\">Bachelor\u2019s in Islamic Theology</cite>, a 2-year Associate\u2019s degree, and specialized <cite id=\"7\">Imam License tracks</cite>. The organization is currently classified as a <cite id=\"8\">sadaqah-eligible institution</cite>, serving as a capacity-building hub for the American Muslim community. Its financial model is characterized by <cite id=\"9\">exceptional fundraising efficiency</cite>, spending $0.00 to raise every $1 in donations. This lean approach allows the academy to maintain <cite id=\"10\">significant liquidity</cite>, holding 48.4 months of working capital to ensure long-term stability.",
